Lab0 highlights:
  Expressions and statements
    Programs are made up of expressions and statements
    An expression is a piece of code that evaluates to some value 
      Primitive expressions
      Arithmetic expressions
    A statement is one or more lines of code that make something happen in a program
      Assignment statements赋值语句
      ——consists of a name and an expression
      ——changes the state of the program by evaluating the expression and binding its value to the name in the current frame.

